      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): surface forum topic names as thread labels",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #7406. Telegram forum topic names were already learned from Telegram topic metadata and exposed as `TopicName`, but the generic session/conversation labels still fell back to the parent group label or group id. Topic-scoped sessions could therefore appear as the same group instead of the actual forum topic name.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nWhen a forum topic name is known, this change passes that name through the generic channel context as both the conversation label and the thread label. Routing remains unchanged: the session key, conversation id, and `message_thread_id` still carry the chat/topic identifiers, and non-forum groups or unknown topic names keep the previous label fallback.\n\n## User Impact\n\nTelegram forum topic sessions now show the learned topic name, such as `Deployments`, in session and thread-label surfaces instead of only showing the parent group label/id. This makes topic-scoped Telegram conversations easier to identify without changing delivery behavior.\n\n## Evidence\n\nHead: `886d9760a3e84397a26066c36274a4370c86fa71`\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.dm-threads.test.ts`\n- `pnpm oxfmt --check extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.session.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.dm-threads.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n",
        "branch": "fix/telegram-topic-session-label",
